    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-29T08:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-29T08:30:00-05:00" n="1091"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1091">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.2546/7–2954: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in India</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_AGV1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Allen</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-29T19:00:00+05:30"
                            >July 29, 1954—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>131. Following several discussions between Embassy and <persName
                        corresp="#p_BDSS1">Bhatnagar</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_JBN1"
                        >Jha</persName>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1091fn1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_JBN1">B.N. Jha</persName> was Secretary of the
                        Ministry of Communications.</note> of <gloss target="#t_MEA1">MEA</gloss> on
                    July 27 handed Embassy representatives note dated July 26 which in effect
                    finalized agreement to memorandum of commitment dated April 10, 1954 regarding
                    purchase thorium nitrate by United States from India (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 24, July 8). Note withdrew <gloss target="#t_GOI1"
                        >GOI</gloss> proposal for amendment clause 4 and expressed agreement other
                    minor textual changes.</p>
                <p>In acknowledging note Embassy confirmed final agreement and stated purchase
                    contract incorporating agreement now being prepared for submission <gloss
                        target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> for its examination. Note expresses hope final
                    signature contract may be effected shortly. <gloss target="#t_TCMI1"
                        >TCM/I</gloss> preparing draft this contract in consultation <gloss
                        target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss>. Text will be submitted Washington for approval
                    prior finalization in Delhi. Please indicate who should sign on behalf <gloss
                        target="#t_GSA1">GSA</gloss>. <persName corresp="#p_JBN1">Jha</persName> and
                    Embassy representatives tentatively agreed no final official text of memorandum
                    of commitment would be prepared incorporating various amendments although for
                    working purposes clean draft would be prepared by Embassy. This arrangement
                    adopted in order avoid any possible budgetary or other confusion which might <pb
                        facs="0716" n="1766" xml:id="pg_1766"/> arise should original memorandum and
                    amended version carry different dates. Texts of notes and documents being
                        airpouched.<note n="2" xml:id="d1091fn2">
                        <p>The notes and related documents were transmitted to the Department in
                            despatch 152, July 30 (891.2546/7–3054).</p>
                        <p>For documentation regarding the discussions relating to the purchase
                            contract and operational agreement, see Department of State file
                            891.2546.</p>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AGV1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Allen</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
